<br>
Kala smiles gleefully at the amazon gaurds on duty. "Yasoo athelfi! It's good to see you." She was happy to be home,she had become homesick. <br>
<br>
The Amazon gaurds saluted thier queen with smiles upon thier faces then stood aside to allow thier queen to enter the village.<br>
<br>
Kala nudges the horse lightly then it steadily canters into the gates. As Kala rode into the village,the two gaurds looked back to see a baby strapped to Kala's back,(Baby backpack!Hehe). <br>
<br>
As Kala reaches mid village,she brings the horse to a full stop and carefully dismounts. A few of the younger amazons run up to Kala grinning happily. "Welcome back Queen Kala!"<br>
<br>
Kala smiles that the youngsters. "Yasoo." The young amazons help Kala get Baby Brook off her back and into her arms,then take Kalas rental horse to the stables.<br>
<br>
Kala craddles baby Brook in her arms.She glances toward the village gates to see if Trinity had arrived yet,and seeing Trin hasnt arrived yet,Kala finds an amazon to take Brook to her hut for a nap,then moves to the center platform of the village and gets on it. She looked around at her athelif then speaks loud enough for most to hear.<br>
<br>
"Yasoo Athelfi! I've returned from my journey." She smiles to them. "And I have some announcments to make,which can wait for now. But I would like to say,now that I am back,I will immediatly start to get things up and running again. I thank you all for your pateince and youve all done a great job keeping the village in tact while I was gone. Thats it." She giggles some. "You all can resume what you were doing." <br>
<br>
